Certain, Odontella aurita. Excellent BLAST and distance tree results. Common in Salish Sea. Certain, Paralia, BLAST and distance tree show both P. sulcata and P. longspina. Distance tree favours P. sulcata (complex). Separating P. sulcata from any other Paralia species is challenging. They are obviously very close species. P. sulcata is the most common reported species (complex) in the Salish Sea. Without SEM and genetic data, hard to separate species.
